11/1/99
  Porting of Reader.
  Why do we need rewindEsByte?
    - to trace firstSlc position: frstSlcTp, frstSlcPos
    - to trace seqHdrEnd position: seqHdrEndTp, seqHdrEndPos
    SeqHdrEnd position is not currently used.
    First slice position is used in copyPesEsHdr().
    Seems we don't really need the rewind capability.


11/2/99
  Modified DPI API for cancel request so that DSP will immediate send back
  ACK/NAK on receiving a cancel request from PPC.  After the actual cancel
  operation is done, the DSP will then send out an indication to PPC.

  Fixed a bug in tsfilter.

  Harmonic Lightway does not gaurantee that each picture has a PES header.
  The packetize() routine, however, assumes each picture has a PES header!
  Problem fixed in rateconv.c by setting outFrmBegin according to the
  payload_unit_start_indicator of the first TP in picture, instead of always
  TRUE.


11/3/99
  Porting of MPEG tools:
      Data structure:
        Splice PicInfo into two parts:
          - SeqInfo for SEQ/GOP which goes to ChanInfo.
          - PicInfo for PIC which goes to PicStat.
        MbInfo should only be used inside the recode routines.
      Note: we assume that SEQ level info will not change.  Otherwise we
            may need to keep different versions of SeqInfo.

      Drop TpInfo and PesInfo structures.

      Note: the definition of frstSlcPtr changed.  Now the first slice
            start code is also copied by copyPesEsHdr()!


