  Memo:
    DPI: signals whether DPI is supported
    DPI_API: signals whether new DPI API is supported.  It may or may not be
             used depending on which PPC code is used.
    dpiApi variable: if 1, means new DPI API is used.  Otherwise falls back
             to old API.


11/16/99

To do:
   Check whether new changes if (!dpApi) works!
   Add DEBUG flags to turn on/off all extra checking codes: done

  Bug: will not timeout in frame-based switching, if signal discontinues before
       enough frames have been received!

  New frame-based splicing implementation:
    Currently frame-based splicing is supported with the variables
    searchStarted and expireTime in ChanInfo.  When the designated number
    of frames have been received, searchStarted will be set, and spliceControl
    task will compare current time with expireTime to detect timeout.
    Problem is that if signal goes out before the designated number of frames
    are received, then searchStarted will never be set, so timeout will
    never be detected.

    The new way to support this is to remove the searchStarted variable, and
    use an estimated expireTime.  As more frames are received, we can fine
    tune the expireTime.

  Debugging decoder:
    DPI Pic 20, mpeg2dec Pic 5, MB 32.
    Trace is correct.
    Prediction MB is differernt.
    Bug Found in reconstComp() in reconst.c: In the bilinear interpolation,
      the casting should be to Uint32 instead of Uint8, because the value
      is a 10-bit number (before >>2).

  Sequence header capture and regeneration:
    We only need to capture latest sequence layer headers.
    We will generate GOP header of our own.

    If a BG picture has sequence header, we will mark the location of the first
    non-sequence layer start code.  All TPs from firstTp to this TP will be
    saved for sequence header regeneration.
    When we delete this picture, we start from the next TP from this marked
    TP.  When we produce encoded bitstream, we start from this marked TP,
    right after the marked position.

  Data flow:
    At splice point, splicer will continue to issue PicStat of the entry
    picture to statmux, and MSG_DECODE_PIC to recodeTask.  Encoding will
    be done in rateConvTask.  After the corresponding entry picture is
    received from statmux, rateConvTask will need to somehow make sure
    the entry picture has finished decoding, and recode the picture so
    as to meet the target rate.


11/17/99
  Seems like we don't need to do sequence header capture if we limit to switch
  only when we see a sequence header.

  To support frame-base switching timeout even when not enough frame is found,
  we initialize expireTime to be localTime + timeout.  It will be updated to
  PET + timeout whenever a new frame arrives until the designated number
  of frames have arrived, then it will be freezed. 

  Possible SEQ/GOP/PIC combinations:
    SEQ + GOP + I_PIC : no recoding necessary
    SEQ + I_PIC : no recoding necessary
    SEQ + P_PIC : need recoding.  Note that GOP header cannot exist
                  in this case!

  GOP header must be followed by I_PIC.


