11/23/99
  Clean up the bitbuf/reader/writer code.

  The entry picture breakup is due to the fact that inverse DC prediction
  is done in reconstruction.  Skipping reconstruction will leave prediction
  undone.

  Replaced Reconstruction with Inv DC prediction.

  Bad FDCT module.  Replaced with module form JPEG group.

  3rd switch is still bad: Missing PIC header in entry picture.
  Bug found in setWriter().  Fixed.

  Bitstream now looks fine.

  Bug: clearBgChan() fails when BG channel has no picture in it.
  Fix: Initialize lastPicStat to NULL in initChan().  In clearBgChan(),
       return immediately if lastPicStat is NULL.
  
  To do:
    - better control of splice time
    - clean vs messy switch


11/24/99
  - Added support for the new message protocol for demux and mux.

  - Picture based splice timeout works now.  Force switch, however, has
    video breakup when audio PID is in use.  There is also no audio.
    When audio PID is not used, video seems to be fine.

  - Progress refresh simulation seems to be caused by the fact that
    the output task is so much behind of the splicer task that when
    the second switch request comes in, the splicer clean up a channel
    whose previous pictures have not been flush out.
    - Modify taskDelay for sun simulation to avoid hugh task timing mismatch.
    - Need to figure out why 2nd splice request is accepted even when the
      channel has not finished outputing.


